WEBVTT

00:01.468 --> 00:02.802
<i>Previously, on "Being Mary Jane..."</i>

00:02.869 --> 00:05.672
My brother's showing me
a listing tomorrow afternoon.

00:05.739 --> 00:08.208
We're not actually having
this conversation now.

00:08.475 --> 00:10.977
Way too early for us
to be even thinking about this.

00:11.044 --> 00:12.312
Well, you haven't met my kids.

00:12.846 --> 00:13.913
Exactly.

00:13.980 --> 00:16.816
Your mom wanted me to make sure
you got in OK. How's everything?

00:16.883 --> 00:18.618
I'm not Ava. I'm Christie.

00:18.985 --> 00:20.320
This is Ava.

00:21.788 --> 00:23.256
- Hey, Paul.
- Hi.

00:23.623 --> 00:26.426
Mom didn't tell me
my new babysitter would be so cute.

00:27.026 --> 00:29.295
- Tell me what you want.
- Tell me you love me.

00:29.863 --> 00:30.864
I love you.

00:31.131 --> 00:32.732
I love you too.

00:32.799 --> 00:33.867
Judge McAlister,

00:33.933 --> 00:36.936
I'm sure you've been approached
by every journalist here tonight.

00:37.003 --> 00:39.439
Then you're aware of my reservations
about interviews.

00:39.506 --> 00:40.573
I am aware.

00:40.640 --> 00:44.144
Now, "Great Day USA"
is friendly and relatable.

00:44.210 --> 00:47.313
It's the perfect chance for the public
to meet the man behind the robe.

00:47.380 --> 00:49.048
<i>So when it comes down to it,</i>

00:49.315 --> 00:50.417
<i>when I look at you,</i>

00:52.051 --> 00:53.620
<i>I see an ugly black woman too.</i>

00:54.421 --> 00:57.457
That's an ambush.
I mean, we're still race baiting.

00:57.757 --> 01:01.094
I think your demeanor is cold.
It's judgmental. It's haughty.

01:01.961 --> 01:05.064
I don't think that's what our viewers
want with their morning coffee.

01:05.331 --> 01:07.901
Look, Mary Jane, we all know
you have charisma and charm,

01:07.967 --> 01:09.702
and that works for the lighter pieces.

01:09.769 --> 01:12.906
It's the serious interviews,
I just don't think they're for you.

01:30.790 --> 01:33.059
<i>- Harvard or Yale?
- Harvard Law, 1976.</i>

01:33.126 --> 01:35.328
<i>- Birthplace?
- Glassboro, North Carolina.</i>

01:35.395 --> 01:38.097
<i>- And the name of his...?
- Mother. Diane, school teacher.</i>

01:38.164 --> 01:40.967
<i>His father, Raymond,
owned a chain of supermarkets.</i>

01:41.034 --> 01:42.769
<i>- And the oldest son?
- Make it bounce.</i>

01:42.836 --> 01:44.971
<i>- What?
- No, I'm sorry. Matthew.</i>

01:45.038 --> 01:46.806
His oldest son is Matthew.

01:47.240 --> 01:50.176
You're about to interview
the Supreme Court nominee.

01:51.077 --> 01:53.546
This could be the biggest get
of our careers.

01:53.613 --> 01:55.682
Yes, and I am more than ready, Justin.

01:55.748 --> 01:57.116
You don't sound ready.

01:57.183 --> 01:59.452
If I'm gonna be stuck
with you as producer,

01:59.519 --> 02:02.121
I need you to recognize
that I do my research.

02:02.188 --> 02:03.156
<i>Prove it.</i>

02:04.190 --> 02:06.359
Judge McAlister is an avid birdwatcher.

02:06.426 --> 02:09.796
He competes in the Ironman competition
every year in Louisville.

02:09.863 --> 02:11.164
<i>He could've been a pianist,</i>

02:11.231 --> 02:13.333
but his mother forced him
to go to law school.

02:13.399 --> 02:15.235
He's a consummate and refined foodie,

02:15.301 --> 02:17.337
<i>but he swears that Hops Diner,</i>

02:17.403 --> 02:19.472
off of Route 25 in Colorado

02:19.539 --> 02:21.875
still serves
the best biscuits he's ever had.

02:21.941 --> 02:23.977
Shall I continue, Justin?

02:24.043 --> 02:26.412
He did the Ironman in Tempe,
not Louisville.

02:29.849 --> 02:31.718
<i>- From the top.
- All right,</i>

02:32.285 --> 02:33.253
let's go.

02:35.655 --> 02:36.589
Too much?

02:37.357 --> 02:40.560
They're coming to enjoy the hotel pool
for a couple hours, not move in.

02:40.627 --> 02:42.428
I just want your kids to like me.

02:42.495 --> 02:44.464
I appreciate that you care. I really do,

02:44.531 --> 02:46.533
but this won't make them like you.

02:47.233 --> 02:50.970
Babe, they're in that middle school phase
where toys aren't cool anymore.

02:52.872 --> 02:55.141
They're gonna be on their phones
all the time, right?

02:56.109 --> 02:57.210
Yeah.

02:57.277 --> 02:58.811
Come on.

03:00.480 --> 03:01.548
It'll be fine.

03:01.948 --> 03:03.149
Just be yourself.

03:03.783 --> 03:06.286
Lee, I know you. If your kids
don't like me, we're done.

03:07.287 --> 03:08.321
Yeah.

03:08.388 --> 03:09.489
No, I'm kidding.

03:10.023 --> 03:12.725
Look, you don't have to worry
about anything.

03:13.259 --> 03:14.661
They'll love you just like I do.

03:15.461 --> 03:16.396
You're amazing

03:18.164 --> 03:19.265
and smart

03:19.732 --> 03:22.235
and beautiful
and intelligent and delightful

03:22.702 --> 03:23.736
and unforgettable,

03:27.674 --> 03:28.908
and I've got to go to work.

03:30.743 --> 03:31.911
See you in the morning?

03:50.530 --> 03:53.166
Good eye. That table's fine real estate.

03:55.602 --> 03:57.270
- You going in?
- You know it.

03:58.771 --> 04:01.608
- Don't wait up for me.
- All right. My man.

04:08.715 --> 04:10.683
I'm a grown woman, you know?

04:11.451 --> 04:13.586
- Excuse me, I'm sorry...
- Do I know you?

04:14.120 --> 04:16.255
PJ Patterson, Comm 101?

04:17.457 --> 04:19.125
Damn, the last time I saw you,

04:19.192 --> 04:21.594
you were rocking sweatpants
and a muscle shirt.

04:22.962 --> 04:25.498
Yeah, that was a long, long time ago.

04:25.798 --> 04:27.033
Sure was.

04:29.335 --> 04:30.737
All roads lead to Manhattan.

04:31.971 --> 04:33.673
- How long are you here?
- I live here.

04:34.307 --> 04:37.210
I'm a real estate agent
at a firm in the city.

04:37.944 --> 04:41.014
That explains
your Armani entourage up there.

04:42.148 --> 04:43.816
Would you like to join us for a drink?

04:44.484 --> 04:47.086
I'm actually headed out.
I have an audition in the morning.

04:47.420 --> 04:49.789
- An acting audition?
- An acting audition.

04:50.056 --> 04:52.325
Okay. You still got that hustle, I see.

04:53.326 --> 04:54.694
We should catch up.

04:55.361 --> 04:57.263
Well, I'll be here tomorrow night.

04:57.530 --> 04:58.765
Maybe I'll see you then.

04:59.065 --> 05:01.668
These guys are always down
for a night of drinking, so...

05:02.769 --> 05:04.070
I'll get you whatever you want.

05:04.904 --> 05:06.539
I do enjoy a bottle of Dom.

05:08.307 --> 05:09.375
I'll get you two.

05:26.893 --> 05:28.327
Why do you have my phone?

05:28.828 --> 05:30.129
I don't have your phone.

05:31.798 --> 05:32.932
What's going on?

05:34.200 --> 05:36.235
Is there any chance I can convince you

05:36.302 --> 05:39.005
to enjoy a morning coffee with me
before you look at your phone?

05:44.644 --> 05:45.945
I'm in "The Observer?"

05:46.012 --> 05:47.313
Don't shoot the messenger.

05:47.747 --> 05:50.750
"Freshman correspondent
at 'Great Day USA' Mary Jane Paul

05:50.817 --> 05:54.120
seeks to oust
veteran anchor Ronda Sales?"

05:54.187 --> 05:55.354
Are you kidding me?

05:56.155 --> 05:57.623
Any chance of that coffee?

05:57.690 --> 05:59.826
"Ronda Sales had her time in the sun.

05:59.892 --> 06:01.694
It's my turn now," says Paul.

06:01.761 --> 06:03.629
They make me sound like a five-year-old.

06:03.696 --> 06:05.298
I didn't even give them this quote.

06:05.364 --> 06:06.365
So who did?

06:08.267 --> 06:09.235
Ronda.

06:18.144 --> 06:21.614
What is with this Mary Jane Paul
and Ronda Sales drama?

06:21.681 --> 06:22.949
Mary Jane who?

06:23.015 --> 06:26.052
She's a morning news correspondent
for "Great Day USA,"

06:26.119 --> 06:29.455
only been there a few weeks,
and now she's trying to take Ronda's job.

06:29.522 --> 06:32.191
So wait, the only two black women
on the show

06:32.258 --> 06:33.760
are now duking it out in the mud?

06:33.826 --> 06:35.828
I wouldn't mind
watching them mud wrestle.

06:35.895 --> 06:37.330
- No.
- Come on!

06:37.396 --> 06:40.399
All right, Mary Jane, what's her deal?
Is she a raging bitch or what?

06:40.466 --> 06:43.269
She must be if she's trying
to go out for poor Ronda Sales.

06:43.569 --> 06:46.839
I mean, this is the woman who hosted
the past four Olympic Games

06:46.906 --> 06:49.842
and has been the face
of morning news since I was a kid.

06:49.909 --> 06:52.145
<i>She's like a national treasure by now.</i>

06:52.211 --> 06:54.247
<i>Maybe she's past her prime.</i>

06:54.313 --> 06:57.383
<i>I mean, Mary Jane's younger.
She's hotter and she's got a...</i>

06:58.217 --> 07:00.319
Should Ty put a white streak
through my hair,

07:00.386 --> 07:02.755
or should I just have him
paint my face green?

07:03.523 --> 07:04.857
Why would he do that?

07:04.924 --> 07:07.426
He gave Ronda
that Glinda the Good Witch hairdo

07:07.493 --> 07:09.996
after she leaked
the story to "The Observer."

07:10.263 --> 07:13.766
I'm just gonna try to embrace
being the Wicked Witch.

07:13.833 --> 07:16.002
Okay, first of all, she got that haircut

07:16.068 --> 07:18.971
because she feels threatened,
not because she leaked the story.

07:19.038 --> 07:20.106
Second of all,

07:20.173 --> 07:23.509
she wouldn't be caught dead within
a ten-mile radius of that gossip rag.

07:23.576 --> 07:25.244
- You don't think it was her.
- No.

07:25.311 --> 07:27.146
She almost sued
a reporter a few months ago.

07:29.215 --> 07:30.383
So it was Justin?

07:34.086 --> 07:37.123
Listen, I have a girl at the tabloids.

07:37.190 --> 07:40.226
I'll call her up and ask
if she knows anything about it, okay?

07:41.761 --> 07:43.095
- I appreciate that.
- Yeah.

07:43.496 --> 07:45.865
I got to figure out
how to repair the damage.

07:45.932 --> 07:47.266
Yeah...

07:49.335 --> 07:50.269
You have an idea?

07:53.072 --> 07:55.808
There are sentences
that start off with conjunctions.

07:56.209 --> 07:58.611
They used the phrase "on fleek."

07:58.678 --> 08:00.813
If you are so offended by it,

08:01.247 --> 08:02.315
help me disprove it.

08:02.882 --> 08:06.018
- Why would I want to do that?
- You're like wounded prey

08:06.519 --> 08:07.987
oblivious to the sharks circling.

08:09.155 --> 08:10.256
That's a stretch.

08:12.892 --> 08:17.363
Okay, suppose I do want to put
this ridiculous rivalry business to rest.

08:18.097 --> 08:19.265
What do you have in mind?

08:20.099 --> 08:22.668
The two of us have lunch
at the corner table at Putney.

08:23.069 --> 08:24.170
A play date?

08:24.637 --> 08:25.972
That's your suggestion?

08:26.038 --> 08:29.375
It's the go-to spot
for all bloggers and tabloid reporters.

08:29.442 --> 08:33.880
I am not gonna risk my reputation
on a bunch of children with iPads.

08:33.946 --> 08:36.749
Those bloggers have ten times
the readership of "The Observer."

08:37.216 --> 08:39.785
Anything they write
spreads like wildfire.

08:40.286 --> 08:42.488
It's high school cafeteria
all over again.

08:42.555 --> 08:44.957
In this business, high school never ends.

08:45.524 --> 08:46.592
No.

08:46.659 --> 08:48.294
I will not stoop to their level.

08:48.761 --> 08:49.695
Fine.

08:50.296 --> 08:51.631
After the Judge interview,

08:51.697 --> 08:54.400
my name will be the only one
people are talking about anywhere.

08:55.701 --> 08:57.036
If he actually does it.

08:57.803 --> 09:01.040
I heard that Gayle King
is making a big play for McAlister.

09:01.540 --> 09:03.476
Can't say that it surprises me.

09:03.843 --> 09:07.413
His handlers are probably advising him
to sit with somebody more experienced.

09:07.480 --> 09:10.016
I have experience,
ten-years-experience at SNC.

09:10.783 --> 09:13.152
Ten years of late-night cable news.

09:14.053 --> 09:15.888
Hard-hitting news.

09:18.324 --> 09:19.292
You're right.

09:20.092 --> 09:21.160
It's probably nothing.

09:23.896 --> 09:25.331
But she does have Oprah.

09:29.068 --> 09:32.405
Screw the haters. She's just jealous
'cause she didn't get the interview.

09:32.471 --> 09:33.839
I know. It's a big scoop.

09:33.906 --> 09:35.474
- Hell yes, it is.
- Right...

09:37.376 --> 09:38.911
- Justin?
- Kara.

09:40.413 --> 09:42.615
Looks like you two
have a lot to talk about.

09:43.049 --> 09:45.351
- I need to call McAlister.
- I already did.

09:45.618 --> 09:48.154
Gayle King was sniffing around,
but he's still on board.

09:48.220 --> 09:50.589
- Still, I should...
- I already have my doubts

09:50.656 --> 09:52.358
about you being able to pull this off.

09:52.425 --> 09:53.859
I got us this interview.

09:53.926 --> 09:55.962
I've completed
all of your ridiculous tests.

09:56.028 --> 09:57.229
I am nothing but prepared.

09:57.296 --> 10:00.333
You're prepared for a softball interview,
and that is changing.

10:00.933 --> 10:02.068
Not now!

10:05.204 --> 10:06.505
Look, I got a scoop.

10:06.572 --> 10:11.043
A trusted source claims McAlister pitted
evidence as a prosecutor in Charlotte,

10:11.110 --> 10:14.380
sending at least one innocent black man
to prison, maybe more.

10:14.680 --> 10:16.515
And this got past everyone in Congress?

10:16.582 --> 10:17.950
They don't have my source.

10:18.017 --> 10:19.118
Who's your source?

10:19.185 --> 10:20.486
You know I can't tell you that.

10:21.754 --> 10:22.788
Your source is weak.

10:23.289 --> 10:25.424
McAlister's beloved
in the black community.

10:25.491 --> 10:27.193
People said the same about Clinton.

10:27.259 --> 10:30.029
His crime bill in 1994
sent more men to prison

10:30.096 --> 10:33.366
- than Nixon and Reagan combined.
- Bill Clinton wasn't a racist.

10:33.799 --> 10:35.534
But maybe McAlister is.

10:36.002 --> 10:38.237
- I need something stronger than a maybe.
- Do you?

10:40.473 --> 10:44.043
Who exposed the Catholic Church
sex abuse scandal?

10:44.744 --> 10:46.045
Lead water in Flint?

10:47.646 --> 10:48.581
Journalists.

10:49.215 --> 10:52.084
We have a journalistic duty
to break this story.

10:52.151 --> 10:53.619
If we do not expose this,

10:54.387 --> 10:56.689
McAlister moves on
to a lifetime appointment

10:56.756 --> 10:58.591
at the highest court in this country.

10:58.657 --> 11:02.595
You expect me to sandbag
the next Supreme Court Justice

11:02.661 --> 11:03.996
on national television?

11:04.063 --> 11:06.565
No, I expect you to eviscerate him.

11:29.989 --> 11:31.090
My God.

11:31.157 --> 11:33.426
- Have you been here all night?
- Practically.

11:33.492 --> 11:35.461
Looks like you need that
a lot more than I do.

11:37.363 --> 11:38.330
Shut the door.

11:43.169 --> 11:44.136
What's up?

11:45.738 --> 11:49.275
Justin has a source
that claims McAlister ignored evidence

11:49.341 --> 11:51.544
to put an innocent black man in prison.

11:51.610 --> 11:52.812
Holy shit.

11:53.579 --> 11:54.814
And you believe him?

11:54.880 --> 11:56.849
I did some digging on my own,

11:57.149 --> 11:58.517
and it does seem plausible.

11:58.884 --> 12:02.221
- So get the source to talk.
- The source won't come forward.

12:02.288 --> 12:04.323
I'm guessing that Justin won't reveal

12:04.390 --> 12:05.858
the identity of the source.

12:05.925 --> 12:09.328
- He expects you to go on air and what?
- See if I can get the judge to crack.

12:09.395 --> 12:11.630
Are you kidding me?
Mary Jane, you cannot attack

12:11.697 --> 12:14.033
a man who's gonna be
the next Supreme Court Justice.

12:14.100 --> 12:16.135
You're gonna look like
loony toon black woman

12:16.202 --> 12:18.270
who has an unsubstantiated bug
up her ass.

12:18.337 --> 12:19.405
I know,

12:19.472 --> 12:22.475
but what I can do is create some doubt.

12:22.541 --> 12:24.810
I can ask McAlister where he stands

12:24.877 --> 12:27.113
on some of the policies at that time

12:27.680 --> 12:30.449
and change the conversation
of the congressional hearings.

12:30.516 --> 12:32.818
- And what if he doesn't bite?
- But what if he does?

12:33.119 --> 12:35.221
I mean, if that guy had a hand

12:35.287 --> 12:37.556
in locking even one brother up
without reason,

12:39.992 --> 12:42.094
I can't let him reach the Supreme Court.

12:42.361 --> 12:43.863
I'm gonna say this now.

12:43.929 --> 12:45.464
I have a bad feeling about this,

12:45.531 --> 12:47.800
especially because Justin
is pushing you to do it.

12:47.867 --> 12:48.968
No, I hear you,

12:49.602 --> 12:52.304
but I've dealt with him before,
and I've learned my lesson.

12:53.472 --> 12:54.640
This time I have a plan.

12:57.343 --> 12:59.745
I am so sorry I'm late.
Are your kids here?

13:00.012 --> 13:01.580
I just have to change really fast.

13:03.215 --> 13:04.250
Sorry.

13:04.316 --> 13:05.751
- You must be Aidan.
- Hello.

13:05.818 --> 13:08.120
- Hi.
- Aiden and...

13:08.187 --> 13:09.588
- Nice to meet you.
- Katherine.

13:09.655 --> 13:11.590
- This is Mary Jane.
- Nice to meet you.

13:11.657 --> 13:12.658
Gosh, she's so cute.

13:13.459 --> 13:14.860
May we go down to the pool now?

13:14.927 --> 13:17.062
Of course. I just have
to change really fast,

13:17.129 --> 13:18.697
and we could head down. Sound good?

13:19.198 --> 13:20.332
- Sounds great.
- Okay.

13:21.300 --> 13:22.902
Come on. Let's get going.

13:24.170 --> 13:25.304
You nearly got her there.

13:26.906 --> 13:27.840
Okay,

13:28.474 --> 13:29.608
I'm almost ready.

13:31.577 --> 13:33.312
- May I ask you a question?
- Yes.

13:33.646 --> 13:34.680
How rich are you?

13:37.483 --> 13:39.718
Well, that depends
on what you consider rich.

13:40.152 --> 13:41.420
Are you richer than our dad?

13:41.487 --> 13:43.689
It's not appropriate
to ask about money, baby,

13:44.523 --> 13:45.558
but yeah, she is.

13:46.292 --> 13:47.359
Why don't you have kids

13:47.426 --> 13:49.295
if you're rich enough to have these toys?

13:49.361 --> 13:51.463
Katherine, you're asking
too many questions.

13:51.530 --> 13:54.333
It's okay. These toys are all for you.

13:54.400 --> 13:57.136
Why don't we go down to the pool
and stop with the inquisition?

13:57.703 --> 14:00.873
You told us to ask her questions
because everything was getting awkward.

14:03.375 --> 14:05.411
You know what is awkward?

14:06.145 --> 14:08.814
Your dad's corny board shorts,
that is awkward.

14:09.415 --> 14:11.784
- Yeah, why are you so embarrassing?
- Come on.

14:11.850 --> 14:14.053
I wear these so I can fit in
with the American dads.

14:14.119 --> 14:16.121
- Would you rather I wore the Speedo?
- No!

14:16.488 --> 14:18.157
Exactly, so no complaining.

14:18.457 --> 14:19.625
Come on, let's go.

14:28.400 --> 14:29.535
Ava, what's going on?

14:30.069 --> 14:32.004
Sorry for making you come
all the way here.

14:32.071 --> 14:34.340
I'm freaking out
about this internship thing.

14:36.041 --> 14:37.109
Tip number one,

14:37.476 --> 14:39.044
don't steal from the liquor stash.

14:40.913 --> 14:42.348
You're right. That was dumb.

14:44.149 --> 14:46.752
It's just everyone is so mean,

14:47.086 --> 14:48.520
and no one seems to notice me.

14:48.587 --> 14:50.022
Not what you're used to, right?

14:50.689 --> 14:53.225
I want to work hard.
I want to do a good job.

14:54.026 --> 14:56.428
I just don't know
how to make a good impression.

15:01.166 --> 15:04.536
My first internship was
at an architectural firm in Atlanta.

15:05.104 --> 15:07.039
I heard my boss was up
for a big promotion,

15:07.106 --> 15:09.541
so the next day I brought her
a bamboo plant.

15:09.608 --> 15:11.110
I can do bribes.

15:11.176 --> 15:13.279
It wasn't a bribe. It cost eight bucks.

15:14.146 --> 15:17.249
It's the meaning that counts.
Bamboo symbolizes good luck.

15:17.950 --> 15:19.051
Did it work?

15:19.118 --> 15:20.719
Turned into my first paying job.

15:22.888 --> 15:24.623
This business is so cutthroat though.

15:25.958 --> 15:28.927
- You have a friend in TV, don't you?
- I do, Andrew Cobb.

15:28.994 --> 15:30.763
He works in reality TV,

15:31.330 --> 15:33.532
but just like you,
he started as an intern.

